
@startuml

class Location {
  - String id
  - String name
  - String description
  - List<Exhibition> exhibitions
}

class Exhibition {
  - String id
  - String title
  - Date plannedStartDate
  - Date plannedEndDate
  - Employee coordinator
  - List<ExhibitionItem> exhibitionItems
}

class ExhibitionItem {
  - String id
  - String itemName
  - String artistName
  - String artworkType
  - List<ArtPiece> requestedPieces
}

class ArtPiece {
  - String id
  - String title
  - String artist
  - String description
  - Collector collector
}

class Collector {
  - String id
  - String name
  - String contactInfo
  - List<ArtPiece> pieces
}

class Employee {
  - String id
  - String name
  - String role
  - Employee coach
  - List<Employee> coachedEmployees
}

' Relationships
Location "1" -- "0..*" Exhibition : contains
Exhibition "1" -- "1" Employee : has coordinator
Exhibition "1" -- "0..*" ExhibitionItem : has
ExhibitionItem "1" -- "0..*" ArtPiece : requests
ArtPiece "1" -- "1" Collector : belongs to
Employee "1" -- "0..1" Employee : has coach (coaching)
Employee "1" -- "0..*" Employee : is coached by

@enduml

---

### ✅ Explanation of Classes and Relationships:

- **Location**: Represents a physical area within the museum where exhibitions are held. A location can host multiple exhibitions.
- **Exhibition**: A temporary display of artworks, with a start and end date. Each has a coordinator and a list of exhibition items.
- **ExhibitionItem**: A specific item (e.g., a painting or drawing) that the exhibition needs. It may request one or more art pieces from collectors.
- **ArtPiece**: An actual artwork in a collector's collection that could be used for an exhibition item.
- **Collector**: A person or entity that owns an art piece. They can have multiple art pieces.
- **Employee**: A museum staff member who may act as a coordinator or a coach for junior employees.

---

### 📌 Notes:
- The `Employee` class has a bidirectional relationship with itself to represent the coaching structure.
- The `ExhibitionItem` has a many-to-many relationship with `ArtPiece` through the `requestedPieces` field.
- All classes are connected logically based on the system requirements provided.

